Pre-Game Insights: Rohit Sharma has already made 711 runs, breaking Sachin Tendulkar's record for the most at a World Cup with a game to spare.
Mohammed Shami is the top wicket taker at the tournament as it stands, despite only playing six matches.
India's dominance has been such that they have not really been significantly tested at any stage in the tournament.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match will take place at Ahmedabad's huge Narendra Modi Stadium, which holds 132,000 spectators.
India vs Australia is scheduled for an 8:30am GMT start time today, Sunday November 19, 2023.
The game will be broadcast live in the UK on Sky Sports Main Event and Sky Sports Cricket.
Subscribers will also be able to watch online via the Sky Go app.
Others: Australia's task is to silence the crowd and get some nerves jangling, as the Black Caps were able to do to a degree in their semi-final clash before falling short.
The key battle will come at the top of the order - the likes of Mitchell Starc and Josh Hazlewood must stop Rohit Sharma, Shubman Gill and Virat Kohli getting off to a flyer.
